# pip-audit waiver ledger — Dependency CVE Scan (security-scan.yml)
#
# WAIVER PROCESS
# ==============
# The "Dependency CVE Scan (pip-audit)" CI job fails on any known
# vulnerability in requirements.txt / requirements-dev.txt that is NOT
# listed in this file. To accept a finding as known risk:
#
#   1. Add the vulnerability ID (PYSEC-* / GHSA-* / CVE-*, exactly as
#      pip-audit prints it) on its own line below.
#   2. Directly above the ID, add a comment block with:
#      - package==version affected, fix version
#      - WHY the risk is accepted (exposure analysis, not "busy")
#      - a removal condition (usually "remove when <pkg> bumped to <ver>")
#   3. Waivers are reviewed in the PR that adds them — an entry without a
#      justification comment should be rejected in review.
#
# Each line below is passed to pip-audit as --ignore-vuln <ID>.
# Lines starting with '#' and blank lines are ignored.
#
# PREFERRED RESOLUTION is always bumping the pin in requirements*.in and
# re-running pip-compile — a waiver is a loan, not a payment.
#
